com.ibm.xmi.framework
Class Namespace

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.ibm.xmi.framework.Namespace
public class Namespace
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents an XML namespace. An XML namespace consists of a namespace prefix and a namespace URI, which uniquely identifies the namespace. You can attach a namespace to any construct in the framework object model, except for extensions and XML elements. The framework ignores namespaces when working with XMI 1.0 files and DTDs, but it uses them if you are using XMI 1.1 and XMI 2.0 files and schemas.
